exhibition_description: This installation comprises about 30 concert posters from the late 1960s, borrowed from a few local collections. It compliments the exhibition "San Francisco Psychedelic" in the nearby Harrison Photography Gallery, which is made up of about 75 photographs picturing the psychedelic musicians. Among the subjects are the Grateful Dead, Jefferson Airplane, and Janis Joplin. Most of these photographs are from the Institute's permanent collection.
